  {
    "name": "Meatbun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/e3/Meatbun.png/revision/latest?cb=20160310052415",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "On A Roll",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Single use. Heals the player for one heart. Grants double damage until the player takes damage.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Heals the player for one heart."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Grants double damage until the player is hit.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "In Exit the Gungeon, the effect will also wear off when the player ascends to the next chamber."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The damage effect is lost if either player is hit in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Co-op",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This effect stacks with itself, meaning that a second meatbun will grant 4x damage, and 3 will grant 8x."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Meatbun may be a reference to the California based gaming apparel brand "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Meat Bun",
              "url": "https://meatbun.com/"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The items appearance roughly matches the logo and mascot of the company, and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " lead designer "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dave Crooks",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has, on numerous occasions, expressed enthusiasm and support for the brand."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Medkit",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/0f/Medkit.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Heals",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Single use. Heals the player for 4 hearts.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Heals the player for four hearts on use."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Heals the player for four hearts immediately when collected. Has no additional effect."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has no effect on "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vampire",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is present on the floor, buying this item from the shop and selling the resulting health is almost always a profit. The exact margin depends on the floor but it is generally a respectable amount."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description refers to the NGO \"Médecin Sans Frontières\" (doctors without borders) but parodied to be \"Médecin Sans Diplôme\" (doctors without diploma)"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Contains a small piece of fairy\" may be a reference to The Legend of Zelda series, where fairies are used as healing items."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Ration",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/18/Ration.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Calories, Mate",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Single use. Heals the player for two hearts. Automatically used if the player runs out of health.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Heals the player for two full hearts."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Automatically used if the player runs out of health.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the player has more than one active item, the Ration has to be the selected active item to be automatically used upon death."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has no effect for "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Ration was an  tier item."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This is a direct reference to the rations from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Metal Gear",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metal_Gear"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", both in terms of its description and function, as well as the auto-heal property."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The pickup quote is a reference to the CalorieMate item in Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater, which is itself a reference to the real world Japanese energy bar snack of the same name."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy \"Pretty Good\" is a reference to a famous quote by Revolver Ocelot in the Metal Gear Solid franchise: \"You're pretty good\""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy \"I need scissors! 61!\" is a reference to one of the quotes the Colonel AI says in Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy \"What A Thrill\" is a lyric from the theme song of Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The connection to Snake Eater further ties into one of the key characters of the game, The Boss, using a Patriot as her signature weapon."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
