  },
  {
    "name": "Weird Egg",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/95/Weird_Egg.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Miracle of Gun",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Using the egg while missing health fully heals the player and consumes it. Dropping the egg and shooting it spawns a gun, item, or yolk creature. Dropping the egg into fire spawns a serpent .",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Using the egg while having empty hearts will restore the player to full health."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dropping the egg and shooting it will break the egg, either spawning a random item or gun, or spawning a harmless slug-like yolk creature that follows the player around until they kill it. The player will only receive an item or gun after carrying the egg through a certain amount of floors.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Going through 2 consecutive floors will cause the egg to start hopping slightly and drop a  or  tier item or gun when broken."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "After 4 consecutive floors, the egg will start bouncing and drop an  or  tier item or gun when broken."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The yolk creature can be jammed, in which case it will damage the player on contact."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dropping the egg into any source of fire goop will spawn an "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "There is a long delay before the serpent spawns; a room with active enemies may well destroy the egg before it hatches."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Like the serpent in the Resourceful Rat's Lair, the hatched serpent must be fed to awaken it."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Pits in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Forge",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " don't count as sources of fire and the egg will be lost upon dropping it in."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dropping the egg on green fire will break the egg and no serpent will appear."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item will carry over to a handful of Gungeoneer pasts, excluding the Pilot's, the Hunter's and The Bullet's, and will be available as a pickup beside the Gungeoneer upon spawning instead of automatically being in their inventory."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "During a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rainbow Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", if the egg appears out of the chest, shooting the egg and breaking it will cause the yolk creature to spawn and all other items to disappear after a short period of time. The player can choose an item before they disappear."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is based on the spotted eggs found in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Pokémon",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series, including the requirement of traveling enough distance for it to hatch. Its name references several egg-related oddities found early in the series, such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Bad Egg glitch",
              "url": "https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Bad_Egg"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Odd Egg",
              "url": "https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Odd_Egg"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Glitch Egg",
              "url": "https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Glitch_Egg"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Phoenix Up"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is possibly a reference to the Phoenix Down from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Final Fantasy",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Whereas other non-gun items sitting on the ground undergo a bouncing animation about once every second, the egg will instead rock back and forth, as it does in the inventory."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Molotov",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/5b/Molotov.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Feel The Burn",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Throws a Molotov that sets an area on fire.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Upon use, throws a Molotov that shatters upon hitting the ground, unleashing a large pool of fire "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " that sets enemies on "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and does continuous damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " When collected, all enemies on screen are set on fire."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Molotov does not function in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gorgun",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " boss room, as instead of shattering upon hitting the water, it will sink harmlessly below the surface."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "As the Molotov deals exclusively fire damage, it is useless against enemies that are immune to fire such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Wisp",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet King",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fire goop will reveal secret rooms, not by cracking the wall, but because the goop is visible in the hallway behind the fake wall."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Fixed Bug In the release version of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Molotov could extinguish the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Fireplace",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Keep of the Lead Lord",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Air Strike",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/a2/Air_Strike.png",
    "type": "Active",
