            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dropped bombs can reveal "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret room",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " entrances by cracking the walls, but will not break the secret wall down completely like other explosions."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug While sliding over "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tables",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", pressing the roll button again will spawn another bomb."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the morph ball bombs upgrade in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Metroid",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metroid"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series where Samus can turn into a ball, roll around, and drop bombs. This item's sprite is very similar the sprite used for the bomb item in Super Metroid."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "y cant u crawl"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to an infamous "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "miiverse post",
              "url": "https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/y-cant-metroid-crawl"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the Super Metroid Miiverse community, where the user asked: \"Y Can't Metroid Crawl\"."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to Supply Drop Beta 3, bombs dropped from Roll Bomb could blast open "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret room",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " walls. This was an intentional reference to Samus' bombs being capable of blasting open secret passageways in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metroid",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", but was ultimately removed as it incentivized the player to spend time rolling against every wall to optimise each floor."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "iBomb Companion App",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/cb/IBomb_Companion_App.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "One For That",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Detonates all explosives and explosive enemies in the room.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Detonates all explosives, explosive enemies, and exploding enemy bullets currently present in the room."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemies detonated include:\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bombshee",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Det",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Grenat",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Mountain Cube",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Mine Flayer",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "'s mines"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Pinhead",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Nitra",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemy projectiles detonated include:\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Beholster",
                  "kind": "shrine"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "’s missiles"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "High Dragun",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "'s RPG"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "iBomb has a very quick recharge so it can be used at the start of every room to get rid of the above mentioned enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Can be used to prematurely detonate explosives fired from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Grenade Launcher",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and other similar weapons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Can be used to trigger powerful effects from items such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank Companion's Ring",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " as it has a quick recharge."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item is a reference to the popular iPhone and iPad Apple products and their many diverse applications (usually refereed to as \"Apps\").\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Ammonomicon's quote for the item \"One For That\" is a reference to the slogan used to advertise these aforementioned products, that slogan being \"There's an App for that!\"."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The appearance of this item is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Pip Boy",
              "url": "https://fallout.fandom.com/wiki/Pip-Boy"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " device from the Fallout franchise.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The sprite for the item is internally named 'Peep Boy'."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Though "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Fuselier",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a bomb-themed boss, it cannot be killed with this item."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Supply Drop",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/af/Supply_Drop.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "I Need Mags!",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Single use. Spawns ammo box.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Upon use, calls in a crate containing  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammo",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " at the players position.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Cannot be used if the player is holding a gun with full ammo."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Spice",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Spice has been used at least once, the crate called in by the Supply Drop has a chance to contain more Spice instead of ammo."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Supply Drops have a "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "very",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " low chance to drop on room clear."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Players can stack multiple uses if they acquire more than one Supply Drop."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Calling in an ammo drop on the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sell Creep",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " grate allows the player to sell the resulting pickup."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug Leaving the room while the ammo crate is still parachuting in will delete the crate, and waste the Supply Drop."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug It is possible to call in a supply drop on the elevator shaft in the entrance elevator room of most "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chambers",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". If this happens, the Ammo pickup will fall down the shaft and be lost."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Ammo Synthesizer",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c9/Ammo_Synthesizer.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Ammo Chance On Kills",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Adds a chance to regain ammo upon killing an enemy.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adds a 10% chance to regain 5% of the currently held gun's maximum ammo (rounded down) upon killing an enemy."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If 5% of a gun's maximum ammo is less than 1 (less than 20 maximum ammo), Ammo Synthesizer will restore 1 ammo when it activates."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Works well with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ancient Hero's Bandana",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " as it will restore 4x more ammo effectively making it easier to not run out."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Works well with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Makeshift Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " if it activates."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, each synthesizer has its own independent chance to trigger, increasing the frequency of ammo regeneration."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Armor Synthesizer",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d3/Armor_Synthesizer.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Play Well, Get Armor",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Adds a chance to get armor upon completing a room.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adds a 10% chance to gain armor upon completing a room without taking damage. The armor will spawn on top of the player."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Synthetic Shield"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Heart Synthesizer",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammo Synthesizer",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", grants a familiar that orbits the player and blocks shots. If all three synthesizers are picked up, grants three familiars.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The familiar follows the player with almost no delay and represents the synthesizer the player does not currently have (i.e. if the player has Armor Synthesizer and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ammo Synthesizer",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", it will appear to be a Heart)."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Heart Synthesizer",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/01/Heart_Synthesizer.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Play Well, Get Hearts",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Adds a chance to get hearts upon completing a room.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player is not at full health, adds a 20% chance to gain a  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Half Heart",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " upon completing a room without taking damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Heart Synthesizer has no benefit for "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as it cannot use hearts. It still does, however, contribute to the synergy mentioned above."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chinese Mobile Version",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the sprite of Heart Synthesizer has been changed to resemble the logo of Chinese game developer "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "XD?action=edit&redlink=1",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the company responsible for the mobile port."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Master of Unlocking",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/37/Master_of_Unlocking.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Play Well, Get Keys",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Adds a chance to get keys upon completing a room.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has a 20% chance to give a free "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Key",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " upon clearing a room "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "if",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " no damage was taken in that room."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In practice, this item can almost fully substitute for infinite unlock items due to the sheer amount of keys it generates (assuming the player has little to no "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ")."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the character Jill Valentine from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Resident Evil",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resident_Evil"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and her ability to pick locks.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The item's name is a reference to an infamous voice line in the first Resident Evil game: \"Jill, here’s a lockpick. It might come in handy if you, the Master of Unlocking, take it with you.\""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The item's appearance is based on Valentine's iconic blue beret, which bears a badge for the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Special Tactics And Rescue Service",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " (S.T.A.R.S.) of which she was a member."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The chance to gain a key is in effect during the first two phases of the Lich, and it is possible to earn a key for defeating a phase and 'clearing' that room."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Utility Belt",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/bd/Utility_Belt.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "All Capacity Up!",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Grants an extra active item slot and increases maximum ammo by 20%.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Grants an extra active item slot."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases maximum ammo by 20%."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Gunnerang"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Boomerang",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", thrown guns deal 50% more damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "M1 Multi-Tool"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "M1",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", M1's reload time is decreased by 20%, and its magazine size and maximum ammo are increased. Movement speed is also increased while M1 is held."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, increases the maximum ammo count and grants another active item slot."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Entering a Gungeoneer's past with Utility Belt in your inventory will cause the gun given in that Gungeoneer's past to have its current ammo set to 1.2x of the gun's usual maximum ammo capacity.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This affects "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Marine",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " with the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Hegemony Carbine",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Convict",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " with the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Tommy gun",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Robot",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " with "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Robot's Left Hand",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Hunter",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " with the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Sticky Crossbow",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This bug does NOT affect "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Pilot",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " or "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Cultist",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", as their pasts don't involve being given traditional weapons, and does not affect "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Paradox",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " or "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Gunslinger",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " as they don't have pasts."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unused and Cut Content/Synergies",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - ("
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "CustomSynergyType.USEFUL_TOOLS",
              "style": "code"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Escape Rope",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it causes an unknown effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item and its synergy with the Boomerang are likely a reference to Batman's utility belt and Batarangs, and possibly his aversion to guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If you enter the marines past with this item its effects might glitch and carry over into the past"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Macho Brace",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/9a/Macho_Brace.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Value For Effort",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Shots are more powerful when coming out of a dodge roll.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "After "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll (Move)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the player briefly gains a yellow aura for 0.4 seconds. The first shot fired with this aura will break it, but deal 30% more damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the player shoots bullets "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "during",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " their dodge roll (either using an item or by firing before coming to a complete stop) they will break the aura prematurely, but will not gain any damage increase. Despite not giving any damage increase, breaking the aura in this way will still tint the players bullet yellow."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Possible Bug If the player rolls again "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "immediately",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " upon regaining control after a dodge roll, the damage increase from macho brace will not be allowed to activate. Instead, after the second roll comes to a complete stop, the player will gain the damage boost from "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "both",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " rolls "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "at once",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ".\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "Using this strategy, the player can gain a theoretically infinite damage boost for a single shot from chaining an unlimited number of rolls. Achieving a large boost from this is extremely difficult however, as if the player stops rolling for even a moment the chain will be broken."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets fired by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Companions",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can trigger the effect of the Macho Brace. This also means that if any companion fires a bullet during the players dodge roll, before they have come to a complete stop, they will break the damage aura."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunboots",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Roll Bomb",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cat Bullet King Throne",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - These items fire projectiles when the player rolls. As a consequence they break the macho braces damage aura prematurely, preventing the player from using it."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When playing as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Paradox",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the glow around the player appears pink and white."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets that are shot by projectiles such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Bullet",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are not affected by Macho Brace."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Pokémon",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "held item of the same name",
              "url": "https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Macho_Brace"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which halves the speed of the Pokémon holding it, in exchange for doubling the Effort Value that the Pokémon gains from battle.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "EVs, short for \"Effort Value\", are a hidden stat that affects stat increases upon leveling up. This is referenced by the Gungeon item's tagline, \"Value for Effort\"."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Does not affect speed\" references the speed-decreasing attributes of the Pokémon item, and \"training to be the very best\" also references the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Pokémon",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " anime theme song."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Macho Brace's appears to be an edited version of  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Triggers",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Throwing a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while Macho Brace is active will make the thrown gun invisible. While it is not impossible to re-collect these invisible thrown guns, being unable to see them makes it considerably more difficult."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
