            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Loot Bag will appear on the Gungeoneer's back."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "PAYDAY 2",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and was added in a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Payday Update",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Doesn't Float",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to the PAYDAY 2 achievement Fish A.I., acquired by throwing a loot bag into the ocean."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Loot Bag is the only member of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "PAYDAY 2",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " item set which appears in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Exit the Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Drill",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/88/Drill.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Sawgeant",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "If used on a locked chest, forces the player to fight two waves of enemies and unlocks the chest if they survive. If used on a locked door, opens it for free.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If used on a locked chest, teleports the player to a large version of the chest room, where they must survive one to five waves of enemies. Surviving the enemies will unlock the chest."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If used on a locked door or trapdoor, unlocks the object for free."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Picking up Drill increases the chance of finding the other Payday 2 items, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Loot Bag",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Clown Mask",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The amount of enemies and waves is determined by the chest quality, usually having less enemies and waves when used on low-quality chests, and up to 5 waves for S quality chests. D tier (brown) chests will have a single wave, with 2-4 enemies. B tier (green) chests can have anywhere from 2-4 waves. They usually have at least 4-5 enemies per wave, but can occasionally spawn 6."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When the Drill is used in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Keep of the Lead Lord",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", there's a chance for it to spawn "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet King",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s chancellor, who will chase the player even if left unharmed.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The same applies for "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Old King",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " chancellor when used in the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Abbey of the True Gun",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It is possible for "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Pickups",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to spawn after completing a wave, including other chests. If the player wants to keep them, they must grab them before they finish all the waves; otherwise, when the room returns to its normal size, the pickup may vanish, if the walls close over it. If it is in the center of the room it will remain."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Drill cannot be used on any chests that spawn after clearing a wave in the special Drill room."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Drill cannot be used on the roof of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "R&G Dept.",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " if a chest spawns there after the boss is defeated."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Using the Drill on a fused chest will extinguish the fuse. However, the chest will appear without a fuse in the enlarged room."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Using the Drill on a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mimic",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will provoke the Mimic and consume a charge with no further effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The room will only return to its normal size once the player is inside the radius of the original room."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Drill cannot be used on the lock that requires the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gnawed Key",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When the Drill is used during a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Challenge Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " run, each new wave receives its own room modifier(s)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Drill appears to, on occasion, fail to render a complete arena, leaving some areas black or untextured; however, the collision remains intact."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Drill can be used on "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Brother Albern",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s chest. The lock will fall off of it, but it still can't be opened without speaking to him."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Chests opened by the Drill are rendered indestructible."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player attempts to use "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Trusty Lockpicks",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " on a chest and it fails, the Drill cannot be used on the chest."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If a chest spawns in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Drill cannot be used. However, it can be used to unlock the special rat chests after the boss fight."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The generated room is considered a different room, so leaving items on the floor before using the Drill will result in them being stolen by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the Drill is used on a Synergy Chest, it will spawn a random item or gun."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to PAYDAY 2, and was added in a cross-promotional event.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Sawgeant is also a reference to a PAYDAY 2 skill called Drill Sawgeant."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The \"followed by expletives\" in its description is due to the fact that PAYDAY 2 drills are notoriously prone to breaking and must be fixed by heisters on a regular basis during a bank robbery, and the lines that characters speak when fixing drills usually contain expletives."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Advanced Gungeons & Draguns Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", enemies spawned by the drill could drop "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coins",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Clown Mask",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/df/Clown_Mask.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Anonymity Aid",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Summons a random familiar with a clown mask who either stuns enemies, protects the player with mini blanks, or attacks enemies with a shotgun. An additional familiar is spawned for each additional Payday item the player has.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Visually changes the players appearance to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Dallas",
              "url": "https://payday.fandom.com/wiki/Dallas"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Payday",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Summons one of the following clown-masked companions;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases the likelihood of finding the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Loot Bag",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Drill",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player carries the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Loot Bag",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Drill",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", an additional clown companion will be summoned for each."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The order that the companions are acquired is random."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammolets",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Houston's mini-"
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are affected by Ammolets."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite being a companion item, Clown Mask "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "cannot",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " be obtained from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Companion Shrine",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". This because the shrine searches for items with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "CompanionItem",
              "style": "code"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " code class, while the Clown Mask uses the class "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "BankMaskItem",
              "style": "code"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Clown Mask and its companions are a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "PAYDAY 2",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and were added in a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Payday Update",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "In "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "PAYDAY 2",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", this particular mask belongs to PAYDAY gang mastermind Dallas. The three different clown companions summoned by the mask are based on Wolf, Chains, and Houston/Hoxton, other members of the gang."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The 'Dallas' player sprite does not have a proper "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "timefall",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " animation for tumbling through time during the end credits of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". As a result, the player character will default to a tumbling skeleton."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chinese Mobile Version",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the USA flag on the Clown Mask and resulting player sprites is censored, changing the red stripes to blue ones. This includes the mouth of the mask."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Playstation 4 Occasionally, after traveling to the Marine's past, the player will be in a glitched state where they retain the appearance of Dallas and dodge rolling no longer provides invulnerability."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug While on the Twitch launch system, buying clown mask has a chance for it to appear in the next shop."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Chain's shotgun bullets can be erased by the players  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Scope",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/74/Scope.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Steady Aim",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Decreases bullet spread by 60%.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reduces shot spread by 60%, increasing accuracy."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "360 Yes Scope"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - While holding "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "A.W.P.",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sniper Rifle",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", spinning 360 degrees before firing makes the shot deal 50% more damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The buff can stack up to 6 times, and each instance of the buff will last for 3 seconds, providing an additional 1.5x damage multiplier for each instance."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If player has several Scopes or "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Lich's Eye Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", the buff can stack 1.5x damage multiplier for each item."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The buff will persist even if the player switches to another gun."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Iron Slug"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Big Iron",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Big Iron fires a single high-damage slug."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "M1 Multi-Tool"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player is holding "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "M1",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", movement speed is increased and M1's reload time is decreased by 20%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Sleuth Out"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player is holding "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "38 Special",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", enemy bullets become slower, but its rate of fire is decreased by 20%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With Scope, most shotguns have incredibly tight spread, making them extremely powerful."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "M1 Multi-Tool"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " refers to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "MIDA Multi Tool",
              "url": "http://destiny.wikia.com/wiki/MIDA_Multi-Tool_(Year_2)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Destiny",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destiny_(video_game)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which grants increased movement speed and boasts a very high reload."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "360 Yes Scope"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "360 No Scope",
              "url": "https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/360-no-scope"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " meme spawned by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_of_Duty_4:_Modern_Warfare"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Scouter",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/fb/Scouter.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Quality Assured",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Shows enemy health and damage done. Increases damage and accuracy. Increases curse by 1.",
    "curse": 1.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Shows enemy health bars. Dealing damage to enemies will trigger a number pop-up showing how much damage was dealt.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Decimal damage numbers will be rounded to the nearest whole integer in their pop-up."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The killing blow dealt to an enemy will only show a damage number equal to the amount of HP it had remaining, not the actual maximum damage the attack could have done."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Bug Dealing over 1000 damage in a single hit will cause the scouter damage number to incorrectly display 1."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases damage by 10%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Decreases spread by 10%, increasing accuracy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Badge",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Turtle Problem",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The Scouter will also show accurate healthbars for these companions, making it easier to gauge how close they are to death."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Mini bosses will not show their health bar."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Scouter can make spotting the original "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Killithid",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " when they split easy as it will still show the damage dealt to the original."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to similar technology in the television series "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dragon Ball Z",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Ritvik\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " seems to refer to Ritvik Bansal, one of the playtesters for "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Why this item bears his name is unknown."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Laser Sight",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/9e/Laser_Sight.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "King Of The Dot",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Decreases bullet spread by 50% and adds a red laser sight to the player's weapons.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reduces weapon spread by 50%, increasing accuracy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adds a laser sight that points where the player is aiming."
