            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite being immune to the damage of enemy bullets, the player will still be dealt a small amount of knockback when colliding with them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Stuffed Star was a  item."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the famous invincibility-granting Super Star power-up from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Super Mario Bros.",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Super_Mario_Bros."
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The item's sprite also bears resemblance to Luma from "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Super Mario Galaxy",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Super_Mario_Galaxy"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Star Friends"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the Polaris's inspiration, the Polar Star from Cave Story."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Boomerang",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/7c/Boomerang.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Usually Comes Back",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Throws a boomerang that travels around the room and attempts to stun all enemies.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Throws a boomerang that travels around the room and attempts to stun all enemies."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Boomerang can locate and target "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mimic",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " before they reveal themselves, making it an ideal tool for finding them out."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the Magical Boomerang from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Legend of Zelda: A Link to the Past",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Legend_of_Zelda:_A_Link_to_the_Past"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The blue and red on the Boomerang and how the sprite is positioned are similar to the color scheme and position on the regular and magical boomerangs from A Link to the Past. However, the boomerangs from that game do not home on enemies and are only able to be thrown a short distance in 8 directions."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Gunnerang"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is likely a reference to Batman's Batarangs. It could also be a reference to the Gunerang from the Borderlands series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Two Boomerangs can be seen among the pile of items that makes up the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " throne in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Shield of the Maiden",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c6/Shield_of_the_Maiden.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Block And Load",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Pulls up a shield to protect players from bullets. Players are immobile while using the shield.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Pulls up a shield that protects the player from bullets and contact damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The player is immobile while the shield is active."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The shield can be active for a maximum of 4 seconds. It will blink right before it's about to go down to alert the player."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Firing a weapon or rolling immediately takes the shield down."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Super Hot Watch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Shield of the Maiden locks the players movement, and by extension time, while active. This makes the item near useless, as time will not progress while it is active."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has Shield of the Maiden active when swallowed by a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tarnisher",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the player will not take damage but will instead lose the item.  The item can be recovered after killing the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tarnisher",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Certain effects like explosions, poison, fire, and electricity can still damage the player through the shield."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It can block the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beholster",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " eye laser."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item's description references the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Bloodborne",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bloodborne"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " item, Wooden Shield."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The shield itself is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Eitr",
              "url": "https://eitrthegame.com/"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shield Night"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to Shield Knight from the game Shovel Knight."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Mirror Shield"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "item of the same name",
              "url": "https://zelda.gamepedia.com/Mirror_Shield"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from the Legend of Zelda series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item's interaction with Tarnishers is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Like Likes",
              "url": "https://zelda.gamepedia.com/Like_Like"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Legend of Zelda",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series, who eat Link's shield."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The shield shares a sprite with the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flying Disc",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Exit the Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Crisis Stone",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/49/Crisis_Stone.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Reload. Reload. Reload.",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "The player is invulnerable while reloading an empty magazine.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Grants invulnerability while reloading an empty magazine."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Human Shield"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Melted Rock",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it causes each corpse to spawn a shield after exploding, similar to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Betrayer's Shield",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It is possible to get infinite "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coolness",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by using "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cigarettes",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while reloading."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A voice says \"Reload\" every time a gun's magazine is depleted."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has a counter-synergy with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Full Metal Jacket",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as Full Metal Jacket still uses blanks during Crisis Stone's invulnerability."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blasphemy",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Crisis Stone's sound effect will play after swinging 6 times at full health, but reloading will not grant invulnerability."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This is a poor item of choice with guns of good reload speed. It is recommended to have this item with slow reload guns, such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "RPG",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Reload voice and the item's name is a reference to the Namco series Time Crisis.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The item's function is also a reference to Time Crisis where to reload you must take cover, which prevents you from being hit by enemy bullets."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The \"Reload\" sound that plays when the player emptied their magazine derives from the same game."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item's name is likely a reference to Chaos Emerald, as it is received after completing "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "NPCs",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Turbo Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which NPC's name is a reference to Sonic the Hedgehog."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Portable Table Device",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/35/Portable_Table_Device.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Know When To Fold 'Em",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Can be used 3 times for each charged. Spawns a small table that can be flipped.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Once charged, this item can be used 3 times before needing to charge again."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Spawns a small "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which can be flipped to provide cover.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The table will be destroyed after taking enough damage."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table Techs",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Item",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Synergies",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are triggered by the tables spawned from this item."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "During the second boss phase of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", flipping a table clears out nearby bullets immensely."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammoconda",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may become stuck on tables spawned by this item."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Comparably to their size, the tables this item spawns are weaker than typical tables."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item's quote is in reference to Kenny Rogers' song, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "'The Gambler'",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Gambler_(song)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Portable Table Device appears in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "animated release trailer",
              "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F07SGMPOO7I"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " for the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Advanced Gungeons & Draguns Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Daruma",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/2a/Daruma.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Good Fortune",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Can be used immediately after dodging a bullet to activate a blank effect.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Can only be used shortly after rolling through a bullet, and activates a blank effect."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Like other active items, Daruma needs to recharge by damaging enemies; it cannot be used immediately after every dodged bullet. However, its recharge is extremely short compared to other items that recharge by damaging enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Whiter Guon Stone"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Daruma's recharge is halved. However, Daruma itself is not part of the synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The blank effect can open secret rooms."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The blank effect can activate the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammolets",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "' effects."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player is also in possession of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Sack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Daruma can still be used, albeit will be a bit odd on when it can be used, as Daruma can either be activated before the sack absorbs the bullets, or the sack deletes them first."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bloodied Scarf",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " also prevents the use of Daruma, as it removes nearby bullets on teleportation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dodge rolling over the balloon used for transporting "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ox and Cadence",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "’s replacement arm will allow the item to be used."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Daruma cannot be activated by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Kill Pillars",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "' jammed ring attack."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to a Daruma doll, a round, hollow Japanese doll modeled after Bodhidharma, the founder of the Zen tradition of Buddhism."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Each time Daruma is used, its appearance changes."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Partially-Eaten Cheese",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/6e/Partially-Eaten_Cheese.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Aged Almost 40 Years",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "While active, the player is invincible and instantly kills enemies they come in contact with.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While active, the player turns into Pac-Man, becoming invincible, granting flight, and instantly killing any enemies they come in contact with. The player can still shoot in this mode.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This item can eat enemies that are usually invulnerable: this includes the "
