              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While the damage multiplier itself does not stack, the chance for the multiplier to be applied per-second does."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The flavor text may be a reference to the common idiom \"one step forward, two steps back\", that is taken from a speech by Vladimir Illich Lenin."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  Possible Bug The special UI icon for Devolver Rounds in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chinese Mobile Version",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " appears blue. This is likely due to incorrect colour encoding issues when saving the file, as the same thing can be seen in other UI textures. It also lacks the Devolver 'D' insignia."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Vorpal Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/2a/Vorpal_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Through and Through",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Whenever the player fires, occasionally fires a special high-damage bullet.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Whenever the player fires a gun, occasionally fires a special high-damage bullet, similar to the critical shot fired by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This crit shot deals 100 damage, and is affected by the player's "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Damage",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " stat."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Critical hits do not travel like normal bullets, but instead instantly strike the closest enemy in the cursor's direction regardless of intervening obstacles. Because of this, critical hits will only interact with enemies. Critical hits cannot reveal hidden rooms, break chests, reveal mimics, explode barrels, etc."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gives beam style "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " a small chance every second while firing to gain double damage for one second, creating random seconds of double damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Snicker-snack"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Excaliber",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it fires a spread of 3 homing shots that deal 20% less damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The beam damage multiplier sometimes granted by Vorpal Bullets does not stack with the beam damage multipliers of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Explosive Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shadow Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Katana Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Devolver Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hungry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While the damage multiplier itself does not stack, the chance for the multiplier to be applied per-second does."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When playing "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Winchester (NPC)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s game, if this item activates, it will not bounce, effectively wasting a shot. It is recommended to drop it before the game to avoid mishaps."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item can be activated by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blasphemy",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s sword beam."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Unlike "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", critical chance does not increase with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coolness",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The chance for a bullet to critical doesn't stack with itself, so having multiple Vorpal Bullets will not increase the critical chance."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This Bullet upgrade, unlike most, actually works with beam guns, but instead of a random chance upon trigger pull, it's a random chance upon holding down the beam."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets shot from companions can be affected by Vorpal Bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets shot from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Heart of Ice",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " after taking damage can be affected by Vorpal Bullets"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The word 'Vorpal' is a nonsense word coined by Lewis Carrol in his nonsense poem "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Jabberwocky",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabberwocky"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The term is used to describe a blade which is supposedly very sharp.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy \"Snicker-Snack\" Is a quote from the actual Jabberwocky poem: "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"One, two! And through and through",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The vorpal blade went snicker-snack! He left it dead, and with its head he went Galumphing back.\"",
                  "style": "i"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Katana Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/ae/Katana_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Folded Lead",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Upon killing an enemy, bullets have a chance to unleash a flurry of slashes along the path of the original bullet, damaging enemies. Increases curse by 1.",
    "curse": 1.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Upon killing an enemy, bullets have a chance to unleash a flurry of slashes along the path of the original bullet, damaging enemies.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If an enemy is killed with a beam style "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Guns",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", Katana Bullets has a 100% chance to trigger."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The area of the flurry pushes the player and enemies away."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The flurry can ignite flammable materials, such as webbing or oil."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The flurry can destroy automatic cart turrets in "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Black Powder Mine",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", much like how explosives also could."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gives beam style "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " a 50% chance every second while firing to gain double damage for one second."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because the flurry pushes enemies and players around, using Katana Bullets can damage the player in indirect and unpredictable ways.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Category:Companions",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " that damage enemies can trigger the effects of Katana Bullets. Due to this, players should exercise caution to avoid being pushed into hazards by the blade-flurries created by their companions."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The blade-flurries can appear behind enemies and push them into the player. Normally this isn't a problem since Katana Bullets does enough damage to kill affected enemies and dying enemies won't damage the player, but there are exceptions. Notably: enemies that explode upon death ("
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Nitra",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Pinhead",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Det",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bombshee",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "), enemies that spawn smaller enemies (most "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Blobulon",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "King Bullat",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ") and enemies that spawn bullets after death (most "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Shotgun Kin",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ")."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The beam damage multiplier sometimes granted by Katana Bullets does not stack with the beam damage multipliers of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Explosive Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shadow Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Devolver Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hungry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While the damage multiplier itself does not stack, the chance for the multiplier to be applied per-second does."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets created by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table Tech Shotgun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can trigger Katana Bullets upon killing an enemy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Blade-flurries can trigger the effect of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sunglasses",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The fact that the item increases Curse while being carried stems from the Gungeon rejecting non-bullet based weapons and items, including swords."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The blade-flurries may recycle code from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Nitra",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s explosion-chain, which would explain their unusual behavior (e.g., igniting oil and spider webs, triggering the effect of Sunglasses, destroying turrets)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite the description, Katana Bullets do not have "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Homing Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, increases the chance of the effect and allows more katana bullets to occur."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Katana",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katana"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a type of traditional curved Japanese sword, renowned for their sharpness and cutting power."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Folded lead\" is a reference to the way katanas are "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "forged",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_swordsmithing"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which involves folding the heated steel during construction."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description and name are a reference to Katana ZERO, another game published by Devolver Digital shortly after the release of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "A Farewell to Arms Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Hungry Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/ff/Hungry_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Hungry Hungry",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Adds a chance for the player's bullets to block enemy projectiles, growing in damage and size as they do so.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adds a chance for the player's bullets to become blue. Blue projectiles will 'eat' any enemy projectiles within a radius of 1.5 tiles around them, destroying them.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "For each bullet 'eaten', the projectile will gain a 10% damage and size increase."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Individual hungry bullets will become 'sated' after eating 8 projectiles, and will no longer consume any more, effectively capping the damage and size multiplier per bullet at 80%."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Doubles the damage of beam style "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Hungry Bullets is usually more effective for guns that fire many bullets in a large spread, such as shotguns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Does nothing against enemy beams, such as those fired by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shelleton",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beholster",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Det",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The beam damage multiplier granted by Hungry Bullets does not stack with the beam damage multipliers of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Explosive Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shadow Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Devolver Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Katana Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player is using the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Phoenix",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", its short-ranged flame burst with each shot can occasionally destroy any bullet the burst touches."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, further increases the chance of the player's bullets to become blue."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The quote \"Hungry Hungry!\" and resemblance of the item to a hippopotamus is a reference to the game Hungry Hungry Hippos."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Heavy Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/71/Heavy_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Thunk!",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Increases damage by 25% and doubles knockback, but halves bullet speed.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases damage by 25%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Halves bullet speed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Doubles knockback."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases bullet size by 25%."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Thrown guns will increase in size, and will remain large even after picking them back up. This is purely a cosmetic effect and has no effect on gameplay."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Due to the higher knockback and slower shot speed, this item can be detrimental with short-ranged guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rocket-Powered Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will mitigate the lower bullet velocity."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Heavy Bullets' slowing effect carries over to the gun used for Winchester's mini-game."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, further increases bullet damage, knockback, and size but decreases bullet speed.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This allows bullets to last indefinitely when fired if many of these items are obtained; however, they won't travel anywhere."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "For some beam type weapons, the bullet animation shows separate, individual laser chunks rather than the whole thing."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Heavy Bullets",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heavy_Bullets"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The icon of the item resembles the appearance of ammunition in Heavy Bullets."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The statement about their colors is a reference to the colorful graphics in the aforementioned game."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Over Dose"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy likely references Doseone, the musician for both Enter The Gungeon and Heavy Bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Massive Effect"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the video game franchise "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Mass Effect",
              "url": "https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_Effect"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Bouncy Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/e1/Bouncy_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Boiyoiyoing!",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Grants bullets the ability to bounce off objects.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Allows the player's bullets to bounce off of objects twice."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Absent Minded"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Membrane",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", its shots bounce 4 times and become homing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bouncy Bullets will also cause tables from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table Tech Rocket",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to bounce."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It works well with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Snowballets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as Bouncy Bullets allows them to bounce across the room and grow to massive sizes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If copies of this item are somehow obtained, each copy allows the player's bullets to bounce another 2 times provided if it has the range to do so."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Some guns with bounce modifiers (e.g. "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sling",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") will further increase their bullet speed/damage off of each bounce."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If used with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mega Douser",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the stream of water bounces uncontrollably through out the entire room turning into what I call \"Spaghetti Time\""
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bouncy Bullets resemble "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rubber Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " resemble "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tazie",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Explosive Rounds",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/5f/Explosive_Rounds.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Mega Blast",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Adds a chance to fire bullets that explode upon hitting an enemy or object.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adds an 8.5% chance to fire bullets that explode upon hitting an enemy or object.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The explosions deal 25 damage."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect can only be triggered a maximum of once per second, making it seem like slower fire rate weapons have a higher chance."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gives beam style "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " an 8.5% chance every second while firing to gain double damage for one second, creating random seconds of double damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Air Support"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Air Strike",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it will cover a massive area when used."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cerebral Bros"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Upgrades the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Bore",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to fire 2 drills."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Reactive"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Makes "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lower Case r",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " spell out ROCKET, BOOM, KABOOM, and POW when fired, and its shots explode."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shot Across The Bow"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunbow",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it fires explosive missiles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The explosions do not harm the player."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Explosions can show secret room cracks when using starter guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The beam damage multiplier sometimes granted by Explosive Rounds does not stack with the beam damage multipliers of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Katana Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shadow Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Devolver Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hungry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While the damage multiplier itself does not stack, the chance for the multiplier to be applied per-second does."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If combined with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Angry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", explosive projectiles won't explode when hitting enemies and will just bounce off of them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If used with a shotgun, each pellet has a chance to explode. Since the explosion damage is fixed, this massively increases the power of shotguns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Explosions can destroy otherwise permanent fixtures to the wall, such as shelving in the mines."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Alien Engine",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " explodes using this round, it leaves a small area of fire."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If combined with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Irradiated Lead",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hot Lead",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Frost Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", explosions have a chance to leave a puddle of their respective element."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Sometimes explosions from the item will not function properly if there is a large quantity of the player's bullets on screen. However, the game will attempt to load every potential explosion missed, even if the player is already several rooms away."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Mega Blast might be a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Xenon 2 Megablast",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xenon_2_Megablast"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Ghost Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/f9/Ghost_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Shoot Through",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Bullets pass through enemies and obstacles.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets pierce through enemies and pass through obstacles (including "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tables",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ").\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Each bullet can pierce through one enemy."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bullets that have pierced an enemy deal half damage."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Ghost Bullets interacts negatively with most explosive "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as rather than exploding on impact with an enemy, the projectiles instead pass through.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "For high damage dealing explosive guns, it may be advisable to drop Ghost Bullets during boss fights, and recollect them afterwards."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bouncy Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Allows bullets to pass through an enemy once, bounce off a wall behind them, and hit the same enemy a second time."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hyper Light Blaster",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Shots from the Hyper Light Blaster will be immediately destroyed upon impacting an enemy, and will not pierce."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Alpha Bullet",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/91/Alpha_Bullet.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "First!",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "The first shot of a weapon's magazine will deal 80% more damage.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The first shot of a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " magazine deals 80% more damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blasphemy",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The damage of Blasphemy is only increased for the first projectile fired after a "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "double tap",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " reload. Additionally, like most modifiers, Alpha Bullet only increases the damage of the projectiles- not the melee swing."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is very effective for guns that have a single bullet in each magazine, as every shot will have increased damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item has no effect on beam-style guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, further increases the damage of the first shot of a weapon's clip."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to Alpha (uppercase Α, lowercase α), the first letter of the Greek alphabet."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "J am"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the Christian Bible, where God repeatedly refers to themselves using the phrase \"I am\", perhaps shown most famously and relevantly in Revelations 22:13, "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the Beginning and the End.\"",
              "style": "i"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Omega Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/4c/Omega_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Last!",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "The final shot of each magazine deals double damage.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The final shot of a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " magazine deals double damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blasphemy",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The damage of Blasphemy is only increased for the sixth projectile fired after a "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "double tap",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " reload. Additionally, like most modifiers, Omega Bullets only increases the damage of the projectiles- not the melee swing."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is very effective for guns that have a single bullet in each magazine, as every shot will have increased damage, as well as guns that have a unique bullet at the end of the clip, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Judge",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item has no effect on beam guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergies Ruby Weapon, Diamond Weapon, and Emerald Weapon are all bosses from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Final Fantasy VII",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Final_Fantasy_VII"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The letter \"Ω\" (Omega) is the final letter of the Greek alphabet and is frequently used as symbolism for the end or finality, and vice versa for Alpha (α) bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "J am"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the Christian Bible, where God repeatedly refers to themselves using the phrase \"I am\", perhaps shown most famously and relevantly in Revelations 22:13, "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the Beginning and the End.\"",
              "style": "i"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Scattershot",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/6f/Scattershot.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Quantity Over Quality",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Guns fire a spread of tripled bullets which deal less damage.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Guns fire triple the projectiles, with each projectile dealing 55% of its original damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player creates a combination weapon where the base gun has a synergy that changes it's form, every time the combined gun is dropped and picked back up its projectiles will be "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "permanently",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " multiplied by 3. This compounds on itself, and can be done multiple times (albeit resulting in extreme performance drops)."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Dumb Smart Bullets"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Homing Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", bullets that don't home in become larger and deal 50% more damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Laser Light Show"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Laser Rifle",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Laser Rifle becomes blue and gold, and fires 3 sets of 3 shots in a spread per trigger pull. Each shot bounces once."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If all projectiles hit, the damage is effectively increased by 65%.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This is significantly easier when used in conjunction with "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Remote Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", accuracy increases or guns that home in on enemies."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A beam weapon used in conjunction with Scattershot will be split into three smaller beams, which will remain constant for as long as it is fired. The angles of spread will be re-randomized if the beam is re-fired."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Explosion damage will not be affected by damage modifiers, including damage reduction. As such, Scattershot will massively buff explosive weapons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Scattershot also allows you to fire 3 bullets with each shot during "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Winchester (NPC)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Despite the reduced accuracy of each shot, this significantly improves the chances of hitting any targets. However, on the fourth shot being fired, when the first projectile is destroyed, the game will end, and however many targets you have destroyed before that is used to determine the quality of the given chest, even if all remaining targets are destroyed afterwards."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Scattershot with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dark Marker",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s charge attack will cause the pellets to miss and not trigger the explosion. However, if the player has the synergy with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Antibody",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", there is an extremely high chance the regular bullets will collide and trigger the blank effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Scattershot was an  item."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "A Farewell to Arms Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", each individual projectile only did 40% of its original damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", if Scattershot is picked up before Helix Bullets, four times the normal amount of projectiles are fired. However, if Helix Bullets is picked up first, six times the amount of projectiles are fired.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Regardless of the amount of bullets fired with Scattershot and Helix Bullets, each bullet does 36% of its original damage."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With either "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Scattershot causes the damage of the resulting critical shot to be tripled due to the chance of critical shots being applied when the gun is fired, "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "not",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " per bullet."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, it further multiplies the amount bullets the player shoots and its spread but also decreases the amount of damage each projectile does."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Irradiated Lead",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/3b/Irradiated_Lead.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Poison Shot",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Adds a chance to fire bullets that poison enemies.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adds a chance to fire green bullets that "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enemies for 2.5 seconds.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The chance for any given projectile to be poisoned is 50% multiplied by the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Effect chance scalar",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " of the players current "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Gun",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ". This means that faster firing guns trigger the effect less often, while slower firing guns are more likely to be effected."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Beam-style guns have a flat 25% chance per second to poison enemies they are shooting."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If an explosive projectile (such as from the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "RPG",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Explosive Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") is poisoned by Irradiated Lead, it will leave a small pool of poison "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " upon exploding."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Emerald Weapon"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to, and named after, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "one of the superbosses",
              "url": "https://finalfantasy.fandom.com/wiki/Emerald_Weapon_(Final_Fantasy_VII)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in  the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Final Fantasy VII",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'Irradiated Lead' is a joke material, as lead is famous for its ability to shield against radioactive emissions, and is notoriously difficult to make radioactive."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
