            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Orbital bombs created by the Battle Mode synergy will explode upon touching most companions. This can result in unexpected explosions pushing the player around at inopportune moments."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunzheng",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If arrows from the Gunzheng reach the end of their range while still in orbit, they will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "still",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " count towards the orbital projectile cap, even though they have been destroyed. This permanently lowers the maximum number of possible orbiting bullets, potentially preventing them entirely if 20 Gunzheng arrows are allowed to despawn in orbit.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect lingers until the player restarts the game. Entering a new "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Chamber",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " or starting a new run does "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "not",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " reset it."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Orbiting bullets "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "can still destroy ",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chests",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Care should be taken when entering chest rooms if any orbiting bullets are still present."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Orbiting bullets do not reveal "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret rooms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", even if they came from a weapon that could."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug In "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Challenge Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", if the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Challenge Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " modifier is active, missed bullets will still orbit the player but will also become enemy bullets. Sometimes, this will cause an orbiting bullet to orbit so closely to the player that it instantly deals damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Homing Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/3d/Homing_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Fire And Forget",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Bullets have a chance to home in on enemies.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets have a 20% chance to home in on enemies.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The chance for any given projectile home in is multiplied by the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Effect chance scalar",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " of the player's current "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Gun",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ". This means that faster firing guns trigger the effect less often, while slower firing guns are more likely to be effected."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The homing ability of projectiles is not overridden, but is significantly weakened by the forced helical motion imparted by Helix Bullets."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item grants stronger homing than "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Crutch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", but does not apply to all bullets."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Shadow Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d1/Shadow_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Double Tap",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Firing a weapon has a chance to fire an additional projectile.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Firing a weapon has a 15% chance to fire an additional projectile."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gives beam style "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " a 15% chance every second while firing to gain double damage for one second, creating random seconds of double damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Combombs",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Each time a combomb is thrown, it has a chance to be followed by a second, shadow combomb."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Casey",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Enemy bullets reflected by Casey have a chance to be doubled."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The beam damage multiplier sometimes granted by Shadow Bullets does not stack with the beam damage multipliers of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Explosive Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Katana Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Devolver Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hungry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While the damage multiplier itself does not stack, the chance for the multiplier to be applied per-second does."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Shadow Bullets will maintain their original trajectory even if the player has another bullet modifier that could change it, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".  However, bullets created by  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Gruber's Bane"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can be guided with Remote Bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player kills an Apprentice Gunjurer with this at the same time it shoots the shot of the enemy will double."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tag line refers to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "a gunplay technique used by soldiers and assassins in real life",
              "url": "http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleTap"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to ensure that a downed opponent "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "stays",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " down. This technique, also known as the Mozambique Drill, involves shooting the enemy once in the head and twice in the chest at point-blank range."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Kage Bunshin",
              "url": "http://naruto.wikia.com/wiki/Shadow_Clone_Technique"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " effect refers to a Jutsu technique from Naruto."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Umbral bullets is a technique used by the Umbra witches in the Game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Bayonetta",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayonetta"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Easy Reload Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/2e/Easy_Reload_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Rolling Reload",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Dodge rolling reloads one bullet.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll (Move)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " reloads a single bullet into the players currently held "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rad Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Reloading by rolling does not reset the damage bonus of the Rad Gun, allowing it to be used at max level indefinitely with minimal effort."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item can be used to repeatedly reload and fire the special last shot of guns like "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "H4mmer",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun can significantly reduce the effective reload times of single-shot weapons by dodge rolling as soon as fire is pressed."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Stout Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/68/Stout_Bullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Up Close and Personal",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Increases damage at close range and decreases as bullets travel.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "At close range, bullets are 50% larger and deal significantly more damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The damage multiplier at close range is based on the projectiles original range stat, equal to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "1.125 + 0.625 * (range - 7) / 15",
                  "style": "code"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", with a minimum multiplier of 1.125x and a maximum multiplier of 1.75x."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Any gun with 22 range or higher will have the maximum damage increase of 75%."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Any gun with 7 range or lower will have the minimum damage increase of 12.5%."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "After traveling 7 tiles, bullets return to their original size, and their damage is halved.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Damage at long range is half the damage at close range - for example, if a gun deals 175% of its original damage at close range, it will deal 87.5% damage at long range."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Decreases bullet speed by 30%."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Thrown guns will also increase in size and remain large after being picked up."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Fat Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", bullets will become extremely large. Upon firing, they may make contact with a wall and disappear instantly."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets with the Stout Bullets effect that are captured by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurer",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " return to normal size before being fired back."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Beam weapons will not decrease in power when further away."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, increases the damage and bullet size at close range but decreases the damage and bullet size at further ranges.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Multiple Stout Bullets causes bullets traveling at long ranges to be even smaller than usual, technically the only item that can create tiny bullets."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The unlock flag in the game's code that determines whether or not Stout Bullets has been unlocked is humorously called "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "BLUEPRINTBEETLE_STOUTIES",
              "style": "code"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy Dwarven Stout is a reference to an identically named item in RuneScape."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Snowballets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/e8/Snowballets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Powder Power",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Bullets increase in size and damage as they travel.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets increase in size and damage as they travel.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bullets gain 2.5% additional damage for every tile they travel."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bullets grow by 10% of their original size for every tile they travel."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The damage increase cannot exceed 250%, no matter how far the bullet flies."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stout Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The damage increase afforded by Snowballets almost entirely cancels out the downside of Stout Bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Angry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Ricocheting off enemies allows bullets to linger in the air longer, gaining more damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Remote control allows bullets to be kept in the air for longer to accumulate damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "150% Damage is reached with 20 tiles; Max damage is reached at 60 tiles or greater."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item's name and primary function is a reference to the popular trope of snowballs increasing in size, often to huge snow boulders, when rolling down a hill."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The \"sole scarf in the Gungeon\" mentioned to in the description might refer to the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bloodied Scarf",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as it is the only item called a scarf in the game."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Remote Bullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/37/Remote_Bullets.png",
