            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " move in a helical pattern."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hip Holster",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The projectile fired on reloading a gun is given helical motion, but is not duplicated."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Roll Bomb",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Rolling will drop two bombs instead of one. Instead of bouncing across the ground, bombs will travel in a short helical arc."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Black Hole Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Singularity",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Helix projectiles are "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "not",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " affected by the gravitational pull of black holes, making it far easier to attack enemies while a black hole is active."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dark Marker",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The charged projectiles of Dark Marker are unaffected by Helix Bullets.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Antichamber"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - Each regular shot of the Dark Marker will fire one matter projectile and one antimatter projectile in a helical pattern. "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "However",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", these projectiles move considerably faster than normal, and do not tend to collide, making the Antichamber synergy almost useless."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Kaliber",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - After converting into soul form, projectiles from the High Kaliber will fly towards the player and stop in front of them, before continuing their initial trajectory. This makes the souls extremely easy to step on."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table Tech Sight",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Double Vision",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Helix Bullets stacks with other items that multiply the players number of projectiles, for example firing four projectiles per 1 original shot while Double Vision is active.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Possible Bug  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Scattershot",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - Scattershot interacts uniquely with Helix Bullets depending on which item was picked up "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "first",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ". If "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Scattershot",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " was picked up before Helix Bullets, the player will fire 4 projectiles per 1 original shot. If "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Helix Bullets",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " was picked up before Scattershot, the player will fire "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "6",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " projectiles per 1 original shot."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This interaction can be manually arranged by dropping and picking back up Helix Bullets and Scattershot in the desired order."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The projectiles of most "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Companions",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "are",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " given a helical motion, but are not duplicated."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Explosion damage will not be affected by damage modifiers, including damage reduction. As such, Helix Bullets will massively buff explosive weapons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When used on a gun with non-zero bullet spread, each shots angle variance will be mirrored between the two helix projectiles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When used by a gun that fires several different kinds of shots at random, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mr. Accretion Jr.",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tetrominator",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", each bullet of the helix will be randomly selected."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item's appearance is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "original Pokémon games",
              "url": "https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Red_and_Green_Versions"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", offered to the player as one fossil, \"the Helix Fossil\", among a choice of two. The other, \"the Dome Fossil\", does not appear to be referenced in game.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The pickup text is a reference to the cult-like following the item acquired during a collaborative stream of these games, called \""
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Twitch Plays Pokémon",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twitch_Plays_Pok%C3%A9mon#Viewership"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ",\" where viewers/collaborators would often quote \""
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "praise helix",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\" as the player, who was controlled by Twitch chat, would often unsuccessfully attempt to “use” the Helix Fossil."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Barrel synergy is a reference to the Dr. Seuss childrens book, "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "One Fish Two Fish Red Fish Blue Fish",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Bumbullets",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/73/Bumbullets.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Bumblecore",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Upon firing, adds a chance to fire a bee, which homes in on and damages enemies.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Every one second while the fire key is held, the item causes the player's gun to shoot a bee which homes in on and damages enemies.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The extra bee projectile deals 3 damage to enemies, and swarms around its target dealing 1 damage two more times before expiring.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "The initial 3 damage impact of the bee is affected by the players "
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "ref",
                      "v": "Damage",
                      "kind": "lore"
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": " stat, but the lingering swarm damage is not."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This extra bee projectile does not consume ammo."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Double Vision",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table Tech Sight",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - These items will also multiply the number of bees created by Bumbullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Angry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - As bee swarm damage is a damage-over-time effect rather than an actual projectile, bees bouncing off of enemies will still leave a lingering bee attacking them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Zombie Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Bees can refund ammo upon hitting a wall, despite not costing ammo to create. This includes bees created by holding fire on charge weapons, allowing the player to slowly restore ammo at no cost."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Charmed Bow",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " +  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Unbelievably Charming"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Bees fired from the Charmed Bow will charm enemies. This includes bees fired by holding down the fire key without releasing, allowing the player to charm enemies without expending ammo."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because bee spawning is based on an independent cooldown while the fire key is held. Holding down the fire key with a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Category:Charged",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "-style weapon allows the player to spawn one bee a second at no ammo cost.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This includes infinite ammo weapons such as "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Casey",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bees spawned this way reveal secret walls, and do not anger the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Shop",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Bumbullets\" is a portmanteau of the word \"bumble\" (as in bumblebee) and \"bullets.\""
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Bloody 9mm",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/1b/Bloody_9mm.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Be Realistic",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Adds a chance to fire a fast, homing bullet that flies around the room damaging enemies.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adds an 8% chance per second for a bullet to be replaced by a fast, homing, piercing, and bouncing bullet that flies around the room damaging enemies."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The chance to fire a berserk round is higher for slower weapons. For example, it is nearly 100% for a fully charged "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "BSG",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item can be detrimental with certain items, such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Black Hole Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", since it completely replaces the gun’s regular shot."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Owning duplicates of this item will not increase its chance of the effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bloody 9mm is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Logen Ninefingers",
              "url": "https://firstlaw.fandom.com/wiki/Logen_Ninefingers"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", nicknamed \"The Bloody Nine\", a major character in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The First Law",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " book series by Joe Abercrombie."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
