              "v": " melee swipe and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Wallmonger",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " body still deal contact damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Electrified "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tazie",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " do not deal damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name of this item has a double meaning. '"
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Live ammunition",
              "url": "https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/live_ammunition"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "' refers to bullets that are authentic and functional (as opposed to blanks), while The Bullet is "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "also",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " 'live' ammunition in the sense that he is a living thing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  Possible Bug The special UI icon for Live Ammo in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chinese Mobile Version",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " appears blue. This is likely due to incorrect colour encoding issues when saving the file, as the same thing can be seen in other UI textures."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Eyepatch",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/b7/Eyepatch.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Hit Harder Less Often",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Increases damage by 35% but decreases accuracy.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Damage",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 35%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Accuracy",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 65%, making shots less accurate.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As this serves as a multiplier on a gun's existing shot spread, guns that are more accurate by default will be less affected. Guns which have 0° of spread by default are not affected negatively by the eyepatch, as any multiplier applied to 0 will always be 0."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the Norse god "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Odin",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Odin"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", in particular the poem "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Völuspá",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of the Poetic Edda, where it is explained that Odin cast his eye into the well 'Mímisbrunnr' in exchange for wisdom. The runes supposedly carved into the eyepatch item are likely in reference to the nordic "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Elder Futhark",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elder_Futhark"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the oldest runic script."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Iroquois"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the 1981 film "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Escape from New York",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escape_from_New_York"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where the protagonist Snake Plissken wears an eyepatch over his left eye and carries a MAC10."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
