  {
    "name": "Unity",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/3d/Unity.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Our Powers Combined",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Increases damage based on the other guns the player has.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases damage based on the other guns the player has.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "2% of the total damage of the player's non-equipped guns is added as flat damage to the player's currently equipped gun."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Captain Plant It"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Portable Turret",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Portable Turret gains Unity's damage bonus."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Garbage Collecting"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Trashcannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", hitting an enemy with it causes it and its bullets to briefly freeze."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "what engine do you use"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gungine",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it fires a spread of three bullets per shot, but fires at 1/5th of its original rate of fire."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Guns that have infinite ammo, including starter guns, are included in Unity's effects."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Unity's effect makes the item especially effective with shotgun-type weapons, as the flat damage bonus is added to each bullet of each spread, effectively multiplying its damage bonus."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "For guns that fire different bullets depending on whether they are charged or not, the attack power of the uncharged bullet is used in the calculation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "For guns that fire different bullets, the attack power of the first bullet fired is used in the calculation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "For guns that have multiple forms, the attack power of the current form is used in the calculation when giving enhancements."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If other passive effects are increasing or decreasing the attack power of the gun, the enhancement value will also increase or decrease."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Makeshift Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " makes a uniquely powerful companion to this item, adding 4 damage to each shot from other guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Wood Beam",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is particularly excellent to pair with Unity, as the flat damage bonus from the item is added before Wood Beam's swing speed multiplier."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Our Powers Combined\" and the ring design is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Captain Planet",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Captain_Planet_and_the_Planeteers"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Captain Plant It"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy also suggests this."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon is built on "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "the Unity game engine",
              "url": "https://unity3d.com/"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", hence its synergy with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gungine",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "what engine do you use"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is a reference to players often asking game programmers what engine they use, and associating the answer with positives or negatives of other games that use the engine."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Garbage Collecting"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  is a reference to \"garbage collection,\" a process by which programming languages or development environments free previously used memory no longer needed by an application. Applications may briefly freeze during garbage collection, which may explain the freeze effect in the synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The ring's name could be a reference to a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "ring of the same name in Diablo 3",
              "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki/Unity"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where multiple players wearing the ring will split damage between each other hence the buff it gives you with more guns."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
