  {
    "name": "Gundromeda Strain",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d7/Gundromeda_Strain.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "All Enemies Weaker!",
    "quality": "1S",
    "effect": "Decreases health of all enemies encountered by 25%.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reduces the health of all enemies and bosses by 25%."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If multiple Gundromeda Strains are acquired (either through cheats or rare edge case glitches) their enemy health reduction will stack multiplicatively: for example, with four Gundromeda Strains, enemies will have 32% of their original health, rather than being reduced to 0%."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item reduces the health of both normal enemies and bosses."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gundromeda Strain's effect is equivalent to increasing damage by 33%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gundromeda Strain allows for quicker kills on bosses due to the bonus not being tied to DPS caps (where additional damage, otherwise, could be ignored)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It should be noted that if too many Gundromeda Strains are acquired, and the player enters the forge, The game becomes unplayable as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " phase two song starts playing, the player can no longer shoot, access their map, switch guns or items, enter the pause menu, use active items, or access the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". If this happens the player can still talk to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", pick up items (such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet That Can Kill The Past",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Pickups",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", but cannot interact with other things such as the boss door leading to the High Dragun. If the player is able to get inside of the boss room though, the High Dragun is stuck in a still shot and is completely invincible. It should also be pointed out that the direction the player faces leads to the bottom middle of the floor's actual area, as the Bloodied Scarf only points here if tried to be used (even though dodge rolling still works normally), even though the player's model points the gun it is currently holding to the bottom right of the player's screen."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item and its description are references to the novel and film "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Andromeda Strain",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Andromeda_Strain"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The icon and effect are a reference to the \"Scarier Face\" mutation from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Nuclear Throne",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_Throne"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The icon closely resembles a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "bacteriophage",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacteriophage"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
