  {
    "name": "Cigarettes",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/5e/Cigarettes.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Hazardous To Health",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Damages the player for half a heart and increases their coolness by 1 per use. Coolness decreases the cooldown of active items and increases luck.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 1.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Damages the player for half a heart. If the player has armor, the damage will remove the armor."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coolness",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1 per use, decreasing the cooldown of active items and increasing the chance of items dropping upon clearing a room. The coolness bonus will remain for the entire run, even if the Cigarettes are removed from the player's inventory."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Discarded cigarettes will light oil puddles and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Phaser Spider",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " webs."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Iroquois"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "MAC10",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the MAC10's reload time is decreased by 33%, magazine size is increased by 50%, and knockback is increased by 50%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "What A Thrill"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Patriot",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Patriot has a chance to transmogrify enemies into snakes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "I need scissors! 61!"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Trank Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Trank Gun changes appearance, its rate of fire is decreased, damage and reload time are increased, and its bullets will inflict "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Armor",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Cigarettes can be used to offensively detonate the blank effect. Consider offensive combinations like "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunknight Armor",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " pieces or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Nanomachines",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dying to Cigarettes will produce \"Smoking\" as a cause of death."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Crisis Stone",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", they can get infinite coolness by using Cigarettes during Crisis Stone's invulnerability periods."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has invulnerability items such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stuffed Star",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Ethereal Form",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", activating it will disable the use of Cigarettes for the duration."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "GuNNER",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Holey Grail",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", they can get infinite coolness by using Cigarettes while holding GuNNER and picking up the skull after each use. Incidentally, this also grants the player infinite ammo for all guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun Soul",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", they can get infinite coolness by using Cigarettes until dying, activating Gun Soul and using its revive effect. It should be noted that the player is left at one heart after the fact, making this strategy risky."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Full Metal Jacket",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and at least one blank, using Cigarettes will activate a blank and prevent damage from being dealt."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Be careful not to use the Cigarettes during boss fights, as using it counts as damage taken, causing you to lose the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Master Round I",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the process if you have not taken any damage prior."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unused and Cut Content/Synergies",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - ("
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "CustomSynergyType.COFFEE_AND_CIGARETTES",
              "style": "code"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgun Coffee",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it causes an unknown effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The heading of the description in the Ammonomicon references the Metal Gear series with cigarettes having the same description."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Convict",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can sometimes be seen using them in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Breach",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Cigarettes are a reference to Metal Gear Solid, where they could be used to make lasers more visible, damaging your health in the process.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Iroquois"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ",  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "What A Thrill"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", and  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "I need scissors! 61!"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " are further references to the Metal Gear series; they reference an alias used by main character Snake, a lyric in a song, and a line of dialogue, respectively."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The packaging of the Cigarettes (namely the red chevron shape near the top of the box) resembles the packaging of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Marlboro",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marlboro"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " brand cigarettes, a ubiquitous cigarette company in the United States of America."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "You can in fact die from overuse of cigarettes. The tagline on the ammonomicon page upon death simply states that the player died to \"smoking\"."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Magazine Rack",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/1b/Magazine_Rack.png",
    "type": "Active",
