    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Place to create a zone of infinite ammo.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Creates a pool of infinite ammo for a short time.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Standing inside of Magazine Rack's radius while holding an empty gun will not let you shoot using that gun. The gun must have at least 1 ammo for this to work."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Just Shoot Me"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Camera",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", this shoots at nearby enemies while active."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Junk Mail"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mailbox",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", activating the Magazine Rack causes Mailbox to only shoot out packages."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Magazine Clip"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Drum Clip",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Magazine Rack's radius doubles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Beam weapons will still use ammo while in Magazine Rack's radius."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item can be used in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Winchester (NPC)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " game to have more than four shots per game."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Just Shoot Me synergy may refer to the sitcom "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "\"Just Shoot Me!\"",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just_Shoot_Me!"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " where the characters work at a fashion magazine and photograph models."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Magazine Rack appears to be a pun on the magazine of a gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While holding "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "GuNNER",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " inside the infinite ammo circle, it will not spawn its blue skull."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Charm Horn",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/3f/Charm_Horn.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "The Call Of Duty",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Charms enemies around the player upon use. Can be used to steal from shops.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Upon use, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Enemies",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " within an 8 tile radius around the player for 10 seconds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Charms all "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Merchants",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " within an 8 tile radius of the player for 10 seconds. While charmed, the player can "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stealing",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from that merchant."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Hornucopia"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Banana",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the exploding banana will send out five bouncing explosive bananas instead of three, one of which explodes into 4 additional exploding bananas. Additionally, using Charm Horn when holding "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Banana",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " fires a banana at each enemy it charms."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If used on the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Misfire Beast",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s projection, the projection will home in on the beast and instantly kill it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Does not affect bosses."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is similar to Boromir's horn in The Lord of the Rings."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tagline is an obvious reference to the popular phrase referring to when people are called to aid the country or comrades."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Cog of Battle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/b9/Cog_of_Battle.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Active Reload",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "When reloading, pressing reload again when the indicator passes a certain mark on the reload bar will instantly reload the weapon, decreasing the reload time and increasing the damage and accuracy of the next magazine.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When reloading, pressing the fire or reload buttons when the indicator passes a certain mark on the reload bar will instantly reload the weapon. The mark on the reload bar is set to be at 2/3 of the length of the reload bar/reload time.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effectively decreases the reload time."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect also increases the damage of the next magazine by 75% and also increases the accuracy of the next magazine."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Missing the mark will lengthen the reload time."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Switching to another gun after succeeding an active reload will remove the bonus."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Klobbe",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - After succeeding an active reload, the Klobbes damage and knockback are multiplied by 10, and the gun gains perfect accuracy for a portion of the next magazine. The amount of the next magazine affected by the bonus depends on how many bullets were reloaded using the active reload. Active reloading a fully empty magazine gives the entirety of the next magazine the bonus.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect persists when the player switches away from, and back to the Klobbe."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blasphemy",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Blasphemy must double-tap reload in order to activate an actual reload bar and trigger Cog of Battle. However because Blasphemy never "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "needs",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to reload, once an active reload has been hit, Blasphemy can keep the damage bonus permanently until swapping to a different gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rad Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The active reload effects of the cog are combined with those of the Rad Gun."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Cog of Battle was a  item."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "All active reload effects (including those of the Cog of Battle) are disabled while the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Challenge Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " challenge modifier is active."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Cog of Battle's name and active reload mechanic are a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Gears of War",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gears_of_War"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Hitting an active reload with the fire button instead of the reload button will both succeed the reload "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "and",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " fire the gun immediately after. This can be very useful for guns with 1 bullet magazines."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "During early stages of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeons",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " development, every "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the game natively had an active reload mechanic to reward skilled players. This was eventually removed and turned into the item effect of the Cog of Battle to make the game easier on new and learning players."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Metronome",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/1c/Metronome.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Better And Better",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Grants a damage bonus for each enemy killed. The bonus is reset if the player takes damage or changes guns.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Grants a +2% damage bonus for each enemy killed. The effect maxes out at +150% weapon damage (75 consecutive kills).\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The bonus is reset if the player takes damage, changes guns, or drops their gun."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Picking up a new gun does not reset the bonus, effectively transferring the bonus to the new gun."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "After each kill, a tone will play and a small note will appear above the player's head. As the damage bonus increases, the tone will become higher-pitched and the note will change color. The note is red when the bonus is maxed out."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adding currently equipped guns to a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Munchers",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will reset the bonus as if switching guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Playing "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Winchester (NPC)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " minigame will reset the bonus."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Receiving and losing the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Windgunner",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sprun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will not reset the bonus."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemies killed by any indirect means, such as through the Burn or Poison "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", being killed by explosive damage, or being knocked down a pit, will not increment this item's bonus.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This includes explosive damage from guns, such as "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Big Shotgun",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " or "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Grenade Launcher",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Arrowkin",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " enemies killed by a gun will increment the bonus. Killing a transmogrified enemy by walking over it will not increase the bonus."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The effect will trigger when killing any enemy, including illusions such as those spawned by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Killithid",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the harmless blob left over by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blobulord",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", chickens, and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Companions and other passive items that fire bullets can also trigger the effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The effect will not trigger if an enemy is killed by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Strafe Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cat Claw",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s explosions, however it will trigger if killed by the impact of the nails."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metronome will reset upon completing the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunsling King and Manservantes",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s challenge if you were given a gun to use for the challenge."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metronome will not reset upon gun swap during Blessed Runs caused by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sorceress",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", making Blessed Runs much easier."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metronome will not reset when the item itself (not the gun you're holding) is dropped, essentially allowing you to swap guns without losing the bonus damage up."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, allows each Metronome to activate their individual effect when the player kills an enemy. If the player takes damage, changes or drops their gun, all of the Metronomes bonuses will reset.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The number of Metronomes represent the number of small notes appearing after a kill. The oldest Metronome's note will appear at the very top while the newest will appear at the very bottom."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The bonus will not reset when switching "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chamber Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " modes"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "item of the same name",
              "url": "https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Metronome_(item)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from the Pokémon series, which works similarly, gradually increasing the damage of a move if used several times in a row."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Honeycomb",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/7c/Honeycomb.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Bee Prepared",
    "quality": "C",
    "effect": "Taking damage spawns bees that seek out and damage enemies.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Taking damage spawns bees that seek out and damage enemies."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Bee Plus"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Jar of Bees",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", taking damage causes Honeycomb to spawn hornets, which travel faster and deal more damage than regular bees. Jar of Bees will also spawn hornets instead of bees."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "BEES"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bee Hive",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the size of the Bee Hive's bees is doubled, their damage is increased by 25%, and the Bee Hive's rate of fire is decreased by 34%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Honeycomb's bees deal the same amount of damage as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bee Hive",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s bees."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Honeycomb was a  item."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has the BEES synergy and dodge rolls with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cat Bullet King Throne",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the bullets fired by the throne will also be doubled in size."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This may be a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Honey Comb",
              "url": "http://terraria.gamepedia.com/Honey_Comb"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " item with the same effect in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Terraria",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terraria"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy with Bee Hive may also allude to the Hive Pack, also from Terraria."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Map",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/43/Map.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Floor Revealed",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Reveals the entire map for the current floor.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fully reveals the layout of the current floor, including "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret Rooms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Map is consumed upon pickup and does not appear in the player's inventory."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has a small chance to drop on room clear."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Does not reveal the trapdoor to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It is possible to sell a map to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sell Creep",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by digging it up on top of his grate via  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Knight's Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A Map can be seen among the pile of items that makes up the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " throne in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Gungeon Blueprint",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/94/Gungeon_Blueprint.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Procedurally Updates",
    "quality": "1S",
    "effect": "Reveals all floor maps for the rest of the run.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fully maps out every subsequent floor."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reveals all secret rooms."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Does not reveal the trapdoor leading to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is linked to Woban, the character mentioned in the Ammonomicon entry for the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cartographer's Ring",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". It is implied that Woban created the Gungeon Blueprint as an ultimate revenge against the Gungeon after the walls of the Gungeon began shifting."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Gungeon Blueprint's pickup quote references how the Gungeon is procedurally generated ingame."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Sense of Direction",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/3a/Sense_of_Direction.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Surprisingly Rare.",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Points in the direction of the floor's exit.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Upon use, an arrow appears that points in the direction of the floor's exit."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Using this item in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will cause the arrow to point in a random direction each time."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item doesn't work in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "R&G Dept.",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", possibly because it has the same layout every time, and the player doesn't leave this floor through an elevator."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Combined with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank Companion's Ring",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Triggers",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Sense of Direction allows for more frequent activation of their powerful effects."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to version "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "V1.0.9",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the Sense of Direction did not work in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Hell",
              "kind": "lore"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the compass in The Legend of Zelda franchise. Contained in every dungeon, it will reveal the location of the dungeon's main boss."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In Enter the Gungeon's pre-alpha, the Hunter started with Sense of Direction instead of Dog."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Duct Tape",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/4e/Duct_Tape.png",
    "type": "Active",
    "quote": "Friend Of Gunsmiths",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Single use. Combines 2 guns by granting one gun the projectiles that the other gun fires.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When used on two different guns sequentially, they will be taped together and combined. The first gun the item is used on will be consumed, while the second will gain the following effects;\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Additional projectiles, taken from the consumed gun, fired alongside the host gun's base projectiles. These additional projectiles have their own separate magazine and consume additional ammo from the host gun."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Additional ammo capacity, equal to the consumed gun's ammo capacity."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If used with a gun that alternates between ammo types (such as the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "M16",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Triple Crossbow",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Trick Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") or forms (such as  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "AC-15",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Triple Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chamber Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "), only the currently equipped ammo type will be used in the newly formed gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Cannot be used on infinite ammo guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reloading a combined weapon will reload all it's magazines, if possible."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Charged guns will still need to be charged when combined with a non-charged gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Most special or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Synergy",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " effects of the consumed weapon will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "not",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " be adopted by the combined weapon. Special effects and synergies of the base weapon are typically unaffected.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The ramping firerate of the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Patriot",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Companion",
                  "kind": "shrine"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " buff given by the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Really Special Lute",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", and the stats granted by the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Super Meat Gun",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " are all examples of 'special' weapon effects that are lost when duct taped onto another gun."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If all the ammo of a combined weapon is already loaded into one magazine, it cannot be loaded into another. This can cause confusion with high-capacity weapons such as the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vulcan Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " which can easily hog all the bullets with its magazine."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The reload time of a combined weapon is not affected by the taped-on gun. This means that weapons with instantaneous reloads (such as the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Demon Head",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") can be powerful duct tape candidates as they lend their instant reload to all taped-on magazines."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Weapons with a magazine capacity of 1 will no longer auto-reload after every shot if they are taped onto another gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Synergies",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " that give the base gun in a combo weapon a chance to fire a special projectile, or that change a weapons projectiles entirely without changing its form will often apply to bullets taped onto the gun as well.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Cactus",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " +  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Cactus Flower"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - Bullets from the taped-on gun also have a chance to be replaced by a special prickly pear."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Lil' Bomber",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " +  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Super Bomberpal"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - All projectiles from the taped-on gun will be replaced by blue bombs from  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Super Bomberpal"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " for a short time after firing a bomb."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "RPG",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " +  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "that &^#$# 'pizza'"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "All",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " bullets from the taped-on gun will be replaced by remote controlled exploding fists."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Dark Marker",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " +  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Antichamber"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "All",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " bullets from the taped-on gun will be replaced by alternating matter/antimatter projectiles."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Guns and synergies that provide a passive bonus to the players stats while held will remain active so long as they are used as the base gun in the combination. These passive stat bonuses will then apply to the extra projectiles from the taped-on gun.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Old Goldie",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - Guns taped to Old Goldie also receive Old Goldie's innate 70% damage boost."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Sling",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - Guns taped to the Sling also deal 2.5x damage to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bosses",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shellegun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "M16",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Triple Crossbow",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Trick Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Combo guns made with these weapons as the base gun will only fire projectiles from the taped gun while in the form that they were initially combined in."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Triggers",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If activated with a combined gun held, Ring of Triggers will only fire projectiles from the base weapon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Balloon Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Glass Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct Tape cannot be used on these weapons while they are in their 'destroyed' state."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Microtransaction Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Taping the Microtransaction Gun onto another weapon will no longer cause it to use  when fired. It will also add 400 to the host gun's ammo capacity, regardless of how many  the player holds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If another gun is duct taped to the Vorpal Gun, bullets from that gun will also have a chance to be replaced by crit-shots. However, if the Vorpal Gun is taped onto a different gun, it loses the ability to crit."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hyper Light Blaster",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Hyper Light Drifter is combined with another gun using duct tape, its laser bullets will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "still",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " restore ammo to the combination gun, regardless of if the Hyper Light Blaster is the base of the combination."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Polaris",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rad Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct taping these guns onto a different weapon will attach each tier of the gun as a different magazine simultaneously, causing the combined gun to act like a shotgun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Triple Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct Taping a high firerate weapon to the Triple Gun allows it to expend ammo faster in the first phase, making it easier to get to the more powerful ammo thresholds. However, this also causes the Triple Gun to expend ammo faster when in its more powerful forms, making them less efficient."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Void Shotgun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Void Core Assault Rifle",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Void Core Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct taping another weapon onto any of the three guns in  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Void Corps"
            },
            {
