          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Face Melter",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If another gun is duct taped onto the Face Melter, the amp left by the Face Melter on reloading will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "also",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " fire projectiles from the taped-on weapon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunderfury",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Gunderfury does not gain experience while duct taped onto another gun. If another gun is duct taped onto Gunderfury, it will lose any extra added ammo capacity from the duct tape combo upon levelling up into a new form."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Patriot",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If another gun is taped onto Patriot, that gun will also increase its rate of fire the longer the trigger is held. This can be hard to see, however, as most guns do not have a large enough magazine size to properly witness it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Turbo-Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If another gun is taped onto the Turbo-Gun, using the Turbo-Gun's reload spam gimmick will replace "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "all",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of it's bullets, including those of the taped-on gun, with powered-up Turbo-Gun shots. Allowing the Turbo-Gun to reload without powering it up will return the taped-on weapon to normal."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Plunger",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct taping other weapons to the Plunger is extremely ammo efficient, as both guns will benefit from the Plungers goop ammo recovery."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flame Hand",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Projectiles from other guns also have their damage and scale multiplied when fired out of the Flame Hand."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Composite Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct tape interacts strangely with the Composite Gun.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the Composite Gun is used as the base of a combination, firing a charged shot will only empty the original clip of the gun. The taped-on gun's magazine will not be emptied."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the Composite Gun is duct taped to a different gun, it will be duct taped as two different three-shot magazines. One clip represents the uncharged shots, the other the charged shots.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "Firing a charged shot with this gun will fully empty the original magazine of the base gun, but will "
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "not",
                      "style": "i"
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": " empty either of the taped-on composite gun clips. The player is able to fire two uncharged shots and two charged shots before needing to reload."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Prize Pistol",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the Prize Pistol is duct taped to another gun during the shooting gallery minigame, the player may continue to use the taped weapon to attempt to destroy the targets, with its additional Prize Pistol shot. The taped gun will retain its added Prize Pistol shot after the minigame ends.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If another gun is duct taped to the Prize Pistol, their max ammo counts and projectiles will be combined as usual, but this will not increase the current ammo of the Prize Pistol, resulting in a pistol with 4 ammo remaining which fires multiple ammo-worth of projectiles each trigger pull. This is actively detrimental to completing the shooting gallery. Additionally, the Prize Pistol will be lost as normal upon minigame completion, taking the duct taped gun with it."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Akey Breaky"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Betrayer's Lies"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Although Duct Tape cannot normally be used on infinite ammo weapons, synergies that apply infinite ammo to a weapon can be exploited to achieve an infinite ammo combined gun. If a weapon is duct taped onto one of the synergising guns before the synergy is obtained (which can be easily done by dropping the other item in the synergy), it will remain a combined weapon once the infinite ammo synergy is acquired. This functionally allows the player to apply infinite ammo to one gun of their choice, while also coupling it with additional firepower."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Rubenstein's Monster"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Any weapons duct taped onto the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "RUBE-ADYNE Prototype",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "RUBE-ADYNE MK.II",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will be lost upon upgrading to Rubenstein's Monster, as it is technically a different gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player creates a combination weapon where the base gun has a synergy that changes it's form, every time the combined gun is dropped and picked back up its projectiles will be "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "permanently",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " multiplied by 3. This compounds on itself, and can be done multiple times (albeit resulting in extreme performance drops)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Void Core Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct taping another gun onto the Void Core Cannon will cause the taped-on magazine to also burst-fire. If the taped magazine is fired again while the main Void Core Cannon's magazine is empty, the taped magazine will fire continuously until it is empty."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Combined guns still only count as one gun when fed to a  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muncher",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Duct Tape may be a reference to the movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Aliens",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", In which the protagonist Ripley tapes together an AR and flamethrower near the end of the film while preparing for a rescue."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Gungeon Pepper",
