              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Iron Coin discount and coolness does not stack with multiple Iron Coins."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Activating the Iron Coin in bullet hell clears the next rooms you enter."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The coin will kill the rats scurrying around outside the entrance to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", potentially making it difficult to find."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item, including the amount of uses it has, is a reference to A Song of Ice and Fire, popularized as the television show, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Game of Thrones",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Game_of_Thrones"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Arya Stark strikes a deal with the mysterious assassin Jaqen H'ghar, who pledges to kill three people in her name. He later gives her an iron coin which she can use, if she desires, to meet with the order of the Faceless Men, and become an assassin herself.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Valar Morgunis\" is a play on \"Valar Morghulis\", meaning \"All men must die\", the motto of the Faceless Men."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Super Hot Watch",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d1/Super_Hot_Watch.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Suuuuuuper",
    "quality": "1S",
    "effect": "Slows down time immensely while standing still. Moving speeds up time back to normal.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Slows down time depending on how slow the player is moving. When standing completely still, time is slowed by 99%.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "One second of normal time takes 1 minute and 40 seconds of standing still with the Super Hot Watch."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Dodge Roll (Move)",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is always considered moving, even if the player is rolling against an obstacle such as a wall. This can be used to progress time while remaining in one place."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rad Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Standing still will also slow time on the Rad Gun's reload, making higher active reload levels easier to hit."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Having control of time allows the player more precise control over their remote projectiles, making it easier to weave them around corners and between enemies mid firefight."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tear Jerker",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Having to move to progress time makes it extremely difficult to use the Tear Jerker, as its projectiles are affected by player momentum."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shield of the Maiden",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Shield of the Maiden locks the players movement, and by extension time, while active. This makes the item near useless, as time will not progress while it is active."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While time is slowed, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " cooldowns are also slowed, making firing difficult. However, the player may still cycle through their gun inventory, allowing them to fire every gun once before resuming the flow of time for high damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The five "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Master Rounds",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " required to unlock the Super Hot Watch do not have to be unique. As such, duplicate Master Rounds acquired via  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Clone",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will still count towards the unlock."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Losing a Master Round via dropping it or giving it to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tailor",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will still count that round towards unlocking Super Hot Watch."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Super Hot Watch can be more easily unlocked in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Boss Rush",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as there are 3 chances to acquire each "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Master Round I",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (excluding the 5th)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Speedrun Mode",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s timer isn't affected by the item's effects."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "SUPERHOT",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Superhot"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which constructs its entire gameplay around the same ability.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The flavor text \"Suuuuuuper\" is a reference to SUPERHOT, where whenever a level is beaten a voice chants \"Suuuuuuper Hot\" on loop."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug Time will not be slowed when sitting in a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Minecart",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", even if the cart is completely still. Bringing up the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Map (Mechanic)",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " screen while in a cart however "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "will",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " update time and cause it to slow down correctly. Doing this will prevent the player from being able to move the cart (and by extension, time), forcing them to dodge roll out of it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug The 95% time reduction when looking through the player's "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " menu "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "overrides",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the time slow of Super Hot Watch. This allows the player to slightly accelerate time while standing"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Dropping multiple items onto the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sell Creep",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " grate while time is slowed can cause some items to not be sold correctly. These bugged items cannot be picked back up, and the player will not receive  for them. To prevent this, it is advisable to sell items one at a time, being sure to resume the flow of time between each one to make sure they are sold correctly."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Drum Clip",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/72/Drum_Clip.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "One Size Fits All",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "Increases the magazine size of all weapons by 50%.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases the magazine size of all weapons by 50%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Does not affect guns with only one round in each magazine, as numbers are rounded down."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Single-round guns gain an extra bullet."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hyper Light Blaster",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Increases the magazine size of the weapon without increasing its maximum ammo, preventing the player from ever fully reloading the clip."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Drum Clip can negatively affect weapons that have special effects on the final shot, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Eye of the Beholster",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If duplicates of this item are somehow obtained, further increases guns' magazine size. Doesn't affect guns with one round."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Holey Grail",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/18/Holey_Grail.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Withered Vessel",
    "quality": "D",
    "effect": "Upon taking damage, triggers a blank effect and refills 50% of the ammo of all the player's guns. Increases curse by 1.",
    "curse": 1.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Upon taking damage, triggers a full screen  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " effect and refills 50% of the ammo of all the player's guns, rounded up."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Makeshift Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Taking damage restores the ammo of the Makeshift Cannon, allowing it to be used many times in quick succession. This allows many "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bosses",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to be killed with ease, at the cost of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Master Round I",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Balloon Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Glass Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Holey Grail was picked up "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "after",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the Balloon Gun/Glass Cannon, it will restore part of the guns ammo "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "after",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the player takes damage, effectively preventing it from breaking.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "does not work",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " if the Holey Grail was picked up first, however this order can be easily rectified by dropping the Holey Grail and picking it up again."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "GuNNER",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Because GuNNER allows the player to heal themselves after taking damage at the cost of ammo, and Holey Grail provides ammo whenever the player takes damage, these two items in combination make the player near immortal- provided they continue to re-collect the skulls dropped by GuNNER."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Prize Pistol",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Holey Grail "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "cannot",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " restore the ammo of the Prize Pistol."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blank",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " effect of this item can open "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret Rooms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item's chest tier might be a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_Jones_and_the_Last_Crusade#Plot"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where the true Holy Grail is a simple ceramic cup instead of a golden chalice."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Dodge Roll developers said in the past that this item may be related to the lore of a later expansion, presumably "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "A Farewell to Arms Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This might either be false, or scrapped, as  didn't have anything related to the Holey Grail."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Blood Brooch",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/3f/Blood_Brooch.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "What Music They Make!",
    "quality": "A",
    "effect": "Heals the player after dealing 1200 damage to enemies. Increases Curse by 1.",
    "curse": 1.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1 while held."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Heals half a heart every 1200 damage dealt to enemies."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Antibody",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Antibody has a chance to double healing received from the Blood Brooch."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item has no effect aside from increasing curse when playing as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item effect is reminiscent of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "rally",
              "url": "https://bloodborne.wiki.fextralife.com/Rally"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " mechanic in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Bloodborne",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bloodborne"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", whereby the player character can regain health by attacking enemies after taking damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item and its synergy with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Trick Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are references to Bloodborne where the old blood refers to the blood of the Great Ones.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Blood Brooch resembles Bloodborne's "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Red Jeweled Brooch",
                  "url": "https://bloodborne.wiki.fextralife.com/Red+Jeweled+Brooch"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The pickup line is a reference to Count Dracula's line, \""
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "listen to them — children of the night. What music they make",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\" in the book and in the 1931 movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dracula",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " .\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It may also be a reference to the Bloodborne character "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Father Gascoigne",
                  "url": "https://bloodborne.fandom.com/wiki/Father_Gascoigne"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", to whose wife the Red Jeweled Brooch described above belonged, and who has a mechanic during his boss fight where he can be distracted with music."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Backup Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/fa/Backup_Gun.png",
    "type": "Passive",
    "quote": "Watch Your Back",
    "quality": "B",
    "effect": "With each shot fired, a second bullet will be fired in the opposite direction that the player is aiming.",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Guns simultaneously shoot forwards and backwards. The backwards firing shots will be significantly less accurate."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Gruber's Bane"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shadow Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " all backward shots have an additional projectile."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Like Shooting Fish"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Barrel",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a fish pops out of the Barrel and fires bullets. The last shot of each magazine fires fish who flop around on the ground and fire at enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Interacts strangely with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Double Vision",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Instead of doubling the backwards shots, a player that activates Double Vision with Backup Gun equipped will fire three shots forwards, and one shot backwards."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With Backup Gun, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dark Marker",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s charged shot's accuracy is decreased, which can cause it to fail as the two projectiles have a chance to miss each other."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Negates the recoil of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mutation",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Grasschopper",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Synergizes extremely well with weapons that can bounce shots on walls or release homing projectiles such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Scrambler",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bee Hive",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Moonscraper",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Works well with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Orbital Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as shots fired backwards which would normally miss will instead orbit the player."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "For some reason, Backup Gun seems to cause the forward shot of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Prize Pistol",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to be inaccurate. It's recommended to drop the item in the room before speaking to Winchester to start the game, although it's possible to drop it during the game by backing up to a wall."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The backward shot originates from the front of the gun, in the same pixel as the forward shot.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This works well with extremely close range weapons, like "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Blasphemy",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Quad Laser",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", and weapons with very large bullets."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Alien Engine",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the gun will also fire an invisible flame backwards, though recoil is not affected."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Does not affect "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Composite Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s charged shots."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Does not affect the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Zorgun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s final shot."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The backwards shots can trigger the multi-shot effect of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shrines",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chance Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " triggers independently for forwards- and backwards-firing rounds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Guns that fire forwards and backwards at the same time like the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Directional Pad",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Face Melter",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " have their damage doubled."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item is a reference to the movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Die Hard",
              "url": "https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0095016/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where the protagonist John McClane tapes his Beretta 92F pistol to his back.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Gruber's Bane"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - is a reference to the primary antagonist of the film, Hans Gruber"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Category:Items",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Category:Passive",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
